# LinksOps Industries Company Documents

## File: company/about.md
```markdown
# About LinksOps Industries

LinksOps Industries is a DevSecOps consulting firm specializing in cloud-native security automation and AI-driven infrastructure management. Founded in 2023, we help enterprises modernize their development pipelines while maintaining strict security compliance.

Our core services include:
- Kubernetes security hardening and monitoring
- CI/CD pipeline automation with integrated security scanning
- Cloud infrastructure as code implementation
- AI-powered threat detection and response systems

The company operates with a remote-first culture, emphasizing automation over manual processes and security-by-design principles in all client engagements.
```

## File: company/mission.md
```markdown
# Mission Statement

LinksOps Industries bridges the gap between development velocity and security compliance through intelligent automation.

## Vision
To become the leading provider of AI-enhanced DevSecOps solutions for enterprise clients seeking rapid, secure digital transformation.

## Values
- Security First: Every solution must enhance, not compromise, security posture
- Automation Over Documentation: Prefer executable code to written procedures
- Continuous Learning: Stay current with emerging technologies and threats
- Client Success: Measure success by client security improvements and deployment velocity
```

## File: employees/remote-work-policy.md
```markdown
# Remote Work Policy

## Work Arrangements
All LinksOps employees work remotely by default. Office space is available in Jacksonville, FL for team meetings and client presentations.

## Equipment Reimbursement
- Home office setup: Up to $2,000 for desk, chair, and lighting
- Internet connectivity: Up to $100/month for high-speed internet (minimum 100Mbps down/20Mbps up)
- Security hardware: Company-provided YubiKey for MFA, encrypted laptop with endpoint detection

## Communication Requirements
- Core collaboration hours: 10 AM - 3 PM EST regardless of location
- Daily standup participation via Slack huddles
- Video-on for client meetings and weekly team retrospectives

## Security Standards
- All work devices must run approved endpoint protection
- VPN required for accessing client environments
- Regular security training completion mandatory
```

