# Employee Benefits Package

## Health & Wellness
- 100% company-paid health insurance (employee + family)
- $2,000 annual wellness stipend (gym, mental health, ergonomic equipment)
- Unlimited sick leave with no questions asked policy

## Professional Development
- $5,000 annual training budget per employee
- Paid time for certification study (CKA, CISSP, cloud certifications)
- Conference attendance: One major conference per year fully covered

## Time Off
- 25 days PTO annually, increases to 30 days after 3 years
- 10 company holidays plus floating holidays for personal observances
- Sabbatical option: 4 weeks additional unpaid leave after 5 years service

## Technology Allowance
- $3,000 laptop refresh every 3 years
- $500 annual software/tools budget
- Company-paid subscriptions to necessary development tools
```

## File: clients/security-requirements.md
```markdown
# Client Security Requirements

## Baseline Security Standards
All LinksOps client engagements must meet minimum security requirements:

### Access Controls
- Multi-factor authentication for all administrative access
- Role-based access control with principle of least privilege
- Regular access review and deprovisioning procedures

### Data Protection
- Encryption at rest for all sensitive data (AES-256)
- TLS 1.3 for data in transit
- Regular backup verification and disaster recovery testing

### Monitoring & Compliance
- Continuous security monitoring with SIEM integration
- Automated vulnerability scanning in CI/CD pipelines
- SOC 2 Type II compliance for all client-facing systems

## Industry-Specific Requirements
- Healthcare: HIPAA compliance with BAA agreements
- Financial: PCI DSS Level 1 compliance where applicable
- Government: FedRAMP Low/Moderate baseline controls
```

## File: services/kubernetes-security.md
```markdown
# Kubernetes Security Hardening Service

## Service Overview
LinksOps provides comprehensive Kubernetes security implementation focusing on production-ready cluster hardening and ongoing security monitoring.

## Deliverables
- CIS Kubernetes Benchmark compliance implementation
- Pod Security Standards enforcement
- Network policies for micro-segmentation
- RBAC configuration with service account automation
- Admission controller deployment (OPA Gatekeeper)
- Runtime security monitoring with Falco

## Implementation Process
1. Security assessment of existing cluster configuration
2. Risk analysis and remediation planning
3. Hardening implementation with zero-downtime deployment
4. Monitoring dashboard setup and alert configuration
5. Staff training on security operations and incident response

## Pricing
- Assessment: $15,000 (1-2 weeks)
- Implementation: $45,000 (4-6 weeks)
- Ongoing monitoring setup: $25,000 (2 weeks)
- Optional: Monthly security reviews at $5,000/month
```

## File: services/cicd-automation.md
```markdown
# CI/CD Pipeline Automation Service

## Service Description
Automated secure development pipeline implementation using GitHub Actions, ArgoCD, and integrated security scanning tools.

## Pipeline Components
- Source code security scanning (SAST with SonarQube)
- Dependency vulnerability scanning (Snyk integration)
- Container image security scanning (Trivy)
- Infrastructure as code validation (Checkov, tfsec)
- Automated deployment with security gates
- Post-deployment security verification

## Security Integration Points
- Pre-commit hooks for secret detection
- Branch protection with required security checks
- Automated security issue creation in project management
- Compliance reporting for audit requirements

## Technology Stack
- GitHub Actions for CI orchestration
- ArgoCD for GitOps deployment
- HashiCorp Vault for secrets management
- Prometheus/Grafana for pipeline monitoring
- Slack integration for security notifications

## Expected Outcomes
- 80% reduction in manual security review time
- Sub-30 minute deployment cycles with security validation
- Zero secrets in code repositories
- Automated compliance evidence collection
```